Package: electpollBR
Title: Download Data on Registered Electoral Polls Conducted in Brazil
Version: 0.0.0.1
Authors@R: 
    person(
      "Marcelo", c("Ventura", "Freire"), 
      email = "mvf@usp.br", 
      role = c("aut", "cre"), 
      comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-1735-2435")
    )
Description: 
    Downloads and tidies up data on electoral polls conducted in Brazil.  
    Due to its impact on public opinion and therefore on the elections itself,
    every electoral poll is required by law to be registered in a
    Regional Electoral Court (TRE, Tribunal Regional Eleitoral)
    and the company that conducts the poll is required to be registered with the
    Regional Statistical Council (CONRE, Conselho Regional de Estatística)
    with coverage in the places where the poll is conducted
    and is required to have a statistician registered with the same Council
    as the technical responsible for the poll.  
    Although there exists a site for querying registered polls at
    <https://pesqele-divulgacao.tse.jus.br/index.xhtml>,
    we download the data directly from the open data site of
    Superior Electoral Court (TSE, Tribunal Superior Eleitoral) at
    <https://dadosabertos.tse.jus.br/>.
